wwpLeosCommunityMIB.name: wwpLeosCommunityMIB
wwpLeosCommunityMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpLeosCommunityMIB.description: The MIB module for the WWP Community specific information.

wwpLeosCommunityTable.name: wwpLeosCommunityTable
wwpLeosCommunityTable.description: Table of read/write Community entries. Multiple Set Operation must be used to create entries in the table. Following objects must be set to valid values to create entry wwpLeosCommunityRights, wwpLeosCommunityStatus. If wwpLeosCommunityName is not set to anything then device will set it to public. If wwpLeosCommunityAddr is not set to anything then device will set it to 0.0.0.0. While deleting entry if this is the last entry with read-only or read-write permission then device will not allow to delete entry.

wwpLeosCommunityEntry.name: wwpLeosCommunityEntry
wwpLeosCommunityEntry.description: An entry for each read/write community. Multiple Set Operation must be used to create entries in the table.

wwpLeosCommunityIndex.name: wwpLeosCommunityIndex
wwpLeosCommunityIndex.description: The index used in the table.

wwpLeosCommunityName.name: wwpLeosCommunityName
wwpLeosCommunityName.description: The Name of Community String. This is mandatory object that needs to be set to create entry.

wwpLeosCommunityAddr.name: wwpLeosCommunityAddr
wwpLeosCommunityAddr.description: The IP Address of the host(s) or the host name with access rights. A value of 0 means that access is allowed to any host. This is mandatory object that needs to be set to create entry.

wwpLeosCommunityResolvedIp.name: wwpLeosCommunityResolvedIp
wwpLeosCommunityResolvedIp.description: This object is set to resolved IP address when wwpLeosCommunityAddr is set to host name. If wwpLeosCommunityAddr is set to ip address then this object will contain same IP as wwpLeosCommunityAddr.

wwpLeosCommunityRights.name: wwpLeosCommunityRights
wwpLeosCommunityRights.description: Rights associated with the Community Strings. The community Name associated with 'readOnly' community Rights will not have any access (read\write) to the readWrite communities.

wwpLeosCommunityStatus.name: wwpLeosCommunityStatus
wwpLeosCommunityStatus.description: To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. wwpLeosCommunityRights must be valid prior to creating entry. The Agent should not let all the comunities to be deleted as this will cause isolation of the device. At least one readOnly community and one readWrite community should always be present.

wwpLeosNotifCommunityTable.name: wwpLeosNotifCommunityTable
wwpLeosNotifCommunityTable.description: Table of Notification Community entries. Multiple set operation must be used to create entries in the table.

wwpLeosNotifCommunityEntry.name: wwpLeosNotifCommunityEntry
wwpLeosNotifCommunityEntry.description: An entry for each notification community. Multiple set operation must be used to create entries in the table.

wwpLeosNotifIndex.name: wwpLeosNotifIndex
wwpLeosNotifIndex.description: The index used in the table.

wwpLeosNotifCommunityName.name: wwpLeosNotifCommunityName
wwpLeosNotifCommunityName.description: The Community String to be used for the notifications. This is mandatory object that needs to be set to create entry.

wwpLeosNotifCommunityDestAddr.name: wwpLeosNotifCommunityDestAddr
wwpLeosNotifCommunityDestAddr.description: The IP address or host names of the host to which notification is to be sent. This is mandatory object that needs to be set to create entry.

wwpLeosNotifCommunityResolvedIpAddr.name: wwpLeosNotifCommunityResolvedIpAddr
wwpLeosNotifCommunityResolvedIpAddr.description: This object is set to resolved IP address of host name if wwpLeosNotifCommunityName is set to hostname. If wwpLeosNotifCommunityName is set to ipv4 then this object will contain same IP as wwpLeosNotifCommunityDestAddr.
